    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paint formulated particularly for the needs of art conservators, typically a retouching paint that is relatively easily reversible. Examples could include solvent-based or resin-based paints.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verf die speciaal is samengesteld voor de behoeften van kunstconservators, meestal een retoucheerverf die relatief eenvoudig is te verwijderen. Voorbeelden zijn verven die zijn gebaseerd op oplosmiddelen of hars.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>特別為藝品修復師的需求所配置的顏料，通常為潤飾用的顏料，比較易於還原。這類顏料包括以溶劑或以樹脂為基底的顏料。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
